 {"id":"bd-qq59x","title":"syscall: timer_gettime deleted timer handle with null output should still return EINVAL exactly","description":"Host glibc returns EINVAL for timer_gettime(timer_id, NULL) after timer_delete(timer_id) succeeds, so the deleted-handle contract dominates the null-output path. Add ABI regression coverage for that precedence.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:40:00.250837246Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-21T09:40:00.250837246Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
